<header>

<div id="instruction">Here are some advantages and disadvantages of cultural tourism, which is the topic of the Writing Task in the next exercise. Complete the sentences by choosing a correct option to fit into the gap (...). There may be one, two or three correct options in each case.
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
<a id="clickme"><img class="imagetask1" src="../media/btn_examtips.jpg" mode="1" id="1002"/></a>
  <br/>
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/set5.2_06.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  
  <ol id="questionList">
   
	<li>Cultural tourism, ... involves people travelling to a country in order to visit its museums and monuments, is generally considered to benefit the country.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t1">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t2">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t3">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t4">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>The money ... is generated by cultural tourism pays for monuments to be restored and new museums and exhibitions to be opened.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t5">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t6">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t7">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t8">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>Local people benefit from the income ... cultural tourism generates.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t9">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t10">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t11">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t12">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>Through cultural tourism, visitors learn about the way of life and traditions of the people ... country they are visiting.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t13">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t14">whose</a></li>
	<li><a id="t15">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t16">that</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>People ... live in the host country also learn from tourists.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t17">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t18">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t19">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t20">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>National monuments and other important sites are often looked upon with great pride by the inhabitants of a country, ... welcome the chance to show them off to visitors.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t21">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t22">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t23">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t24">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>Some countries ... monuments have great religious or cultural significance do not want to attract large numbers of tourists.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t25">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t26">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t27">whose</a></li>
	<li><a id="t28">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>Monuments ... are fragile, such as ancient temples or cave paintings, can be damaged by large numbers of tourists.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t29">who</a></li>
	<li><a id="t30">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t31">that</a></li>
	<li><a id="t32">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>At the height of the tourist season, ... monuments receive large numbers of visitors, they require extra protection.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t33">when</a></li>
	<li><a id="t34">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t35">where</a></li>
	<li><a id="t36">(...)</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	
	<li>Small towns and seaside resorts ... large modern hotels are built may lose their unique local character forever.
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t37">when</a></li>
	<li><a id="t38">which</a></li>
	<li><a id="t39">where</a></li>
	<li><a id="t40">whose</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
  
  </ol>
